Citation.sAbstract: The prhoT (pressure density temperature) properties of HFO-1336mzz(E) (trans-1,1,1,4,4,4-hexafluoro-2-butene) is measured by the isochoric method. A total of 154 pT property data points are obtained at temperatures from 323 to 523 K and pressures up to 10 MPa along 19 isochores at densities from 84 kg*m 3 to 1212 kg*m 3. The Benedict Webb Rubin Starling equation of state is used to correlate the present data. Saturated temperatures are analytically determined at 15 state points by extrapolating the isochores to intersect with the vapor pressure curve.
